"{\"statement\": \"Task: Given an array of integers nums, find the pivot index of the array. The pivot index is defined as the index where the sum of the numbers to the left of the index is equal to the sum of the numbers to the right of the index. If no such index exists, return -1. If there are multiple pivot indexes, return the left-most pivot index.\\n\\nInput: The input is an array of integers called nums, where the length of the array is n. Each element of nums is an integer in the range [-1000, 1000]. The input is provided through standard input.\\n\\nOutput: The output is a single integer representing the pivot index of the array. If no such index exists, return -1. If there are multiple pivot indexes, return the left-most pivot index.\\n\\nConstraints: The length of the array will be between 0 and 10000, and each element of the array will be an integer in the range [-1000, 1000].\", \"editorial\": \"\", \"tag\": \"['Data structures', 'Range queries']\", \"difficulties\": \"EASY\", \"source\": \"leetcode\", \"url\": \"https://leetcode.com/problems/find-pivot-index/\", \"sample_test_cases\": [{\"input\": [[1, 7, 3, 6, 5, 6]], \"output\": 3}]}"